{"sessionId":"f064e3","location":"life-updates.ts:parseUpdateWithAI:entry","message":"parseUpdateWithAI called","data":{"rawInput":"If we’re talking tactical, we’re talking efficiency. Twenty years with Buzz means V has a routine tuned like a high-end Sandevistan—no wasted movement, no unnecessary risks, just discipline.\n\nHere is the 24-hour combat-and-domestic log for V.\n\n05:00 | System Boot\n05:00: Internal alarm triggers. Immediate optics check. Wake up next to Buzz. Minimal movement to avoid waking him.\n\n05:15: Hydration (500ml). Pre-workout stim-hit (low grade).\n\n05:30: Tactical Gym Session. Focus on high-intensity interval training (HIIT).\n\n45 mins: Heavy bag work (simulating urban CQC).\n\n15 mins: Core stability.\n\n100 Pushups (Standard, explosive).\n\n06:30 | Maintenance & Intel\n06:30: Cold shower. Chrome diagnostics run.\n\n06:45: Breakfast with Buzz. Real protein, black coffee. 20-minute verbal sync on the day's logistics (bills, apartment security, his schedule).\n\n07:30: Gear check. Loadout: Unity (silenced), Arasaka thermal blade. Check encrypted inbox for fixer briefs.\n\n08:00 – 18:00 | Operational Window\n08:00: Transit to Watson. Low-profile behavior.\n\n09:30: Contract 1: Security audit for a private data-fortress. No casualties, clean exit.\n\n12:00: Mid-day rations. Check-in ping to Buzz (Encrypted).\n\n13:30: Contract 2: Asset recovery in Heywood. Neutralized three Tiger Claw scavs via non-lethal takedowns. Recovered the shard.\n\n16:00: Meeting with El Capitan. Negotiation for long-term passive income ops.\n\n17:30: Ammo resupply and gear repair.\n\n18:30 | Ingress & Debrief\n18:30: Return to Megabuilding. Multi-factor authentication at the door.\n\n19:00: 100 Pushups (Diamond grip).\n\n19:15: \"Off-duty\" status initiated. Vest off. Chrome set to \"Passive/Home\" mode.\n\n20:00 – 23:00 | Sustenance & Recovery\n20:00: Dinner with Buzz. High-calorie intake to offset the day's exertion.\n\n21:30: Quality time. No tech, no holos, no fixers. After 20 years, this is the most critical part of the maintenance cycle.\n\n23:00: Final perimeter check via internal HUD.\n\n23:30: System Sleep. Buzz is the last thing I see before the optics go dark.","apiKeyPresent":true},"timestamp":1773314163857,"hypothesisId":"H1"}
